sermone latino (1515), dividing the history of the language into four periods,
‘most ancient’, ‘ancient’, ‘perfect’ and ‘imperfect’, a division followed by
later writers such as Angelo Rocca in his Osservazioni intorno alia bellezza
della lingua Latina (1590). In 1538, the French scholar Guillaume Postel
