that seemed to be on the rise around the year 1500 was overtaken by rivals
in the course of the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries.
The first example is that of Dutch. In the later sixteenth century, when
the seven provinces of the northern Netherlands became independent,
there were signs of a glorious future for the language. Stevin’s manifesto
