The Germans, the Dutch and the Portuguese also debated these questions
in the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries. A treatise on Danish spelling
was published in 1678, while Peter the Great personally reformed Russian
orthography at the beginning of the eighteenth century (the tsar’s correc¬
