Italian a ‘dead language’, like Latin. It has been calculated that when Italy
became a single nation in i860, only 2.5 per cent of the population knew
and used the standard language.30
In France and England, on the other hand, the victory of the dialects of
the lie de France and the Home Counties seems to have been the result of
a mixture of urbanization and political centralization.
